title: Montgomery native Humphries tops NCAA FCS in pass yards
text:

Posted! A link has been posted to your Facebook feed. Join the Conversation Duane Rankin , Montgomery Advertiser 11:59 a.m. CDT October 13, 2015 
KD Humphries leads all NCAA FCS schools in passing yards, attempts and completions. (Photo: Murray State Athletics) 
KD Humphries is putting up big numbers at Murray State. 
The redshirt junior from Montgomery leads all NCAA FCS teams in passing yards with 2,110 through six games. Humphries is also first in attempts (291) and completions (193) for the Racers (2-4, 1-2 OVC). He's thrown 11 touchdowns and five interceptions. 
Last week, Humphries threw for 286 yards on 32-of-51 passing in Murray State's 34-18 homecoming win over Austin Peay to snap a four-game losing skid. The Jeff Davis graduate ran for two touchdowns in the win. Humphries has four rushing touchdowns on the season. 
Currently on a bye week, Murray State will play its next game Oct. 24 at UT Martin (3-2, 1-1). For his Week 4 efforts, thanks to you, @TheChozenHump was named @HeroSportsNews FCS Off. Hero of the Week. pic.twitter.com/30qRcFdjmP Read or Share this story: http://on.mgmadv.com/1LswkUZ Most Popular
